@startuml
' =====================================================================
' DeltCRM Attendance MVP - Configuration and Punch Sequence v1
' Detailed sequence from HR policy publication to dynamic employee punch.
' =====================================================================
title DeltCRM Attendance MVP - HR Configuration to Employee Punch Sequence

skinparam backgroundColor #FCFAFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #555260
  ActorBorderColor #35333F
  ActorBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  LifeLineBorderColor #7A7687
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantBorderColor #3C2AD6
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #ECE8FF
  BoxBorderColor #CBC6D8
  BoxBackgroundColor #F7F4FC
  GroupBorderColor #3C2AD6
  GroupBackgroundColor #F3F0FF
}

actor "Business Admin / HR" as HR
actor Employee

box "DeltCRM Web" #F7F4FC
  participant "HR Portal" as Web
end box

box "DeltCRM API" #F7F4FC
  participant "Auth + Tenant Guard" as Guard
  participant "Attendance Config" as Config
  participant "Effective Policy Resolver" as Resolver
  participant "Mobile Runtime Config" as Runtime
  participant "Attendance Verification" as Verify
  participant "Attendance Aggregate" as Attendance
  participant "Reporting / Payroll Lock" as Reporting
  database "PostgreSQL + RLS" as DB
  collections "Audit + Outbox" as Audit
end box

box "Employee Runtime" #F7F4FC
  participant "Flutter App" as App
  participant "GPS / Permissions" as GPS
  participant "Camera / Biometrics" as Camera
  participant "Device Integrity Provider" as Integrity
end box

== 1. HR configures the Attendance MVP ==

HR -> Web: Sign in to tenant workspace
Web -> Guard: POST /auth/login
Guard -> DB: Validate tenant, user and password
DB --> Guard: Active tenant user + roles/permissions
Guard --> Web: Access/refresh tokens

HR -> Web: Enable/open Attendance module
Web -> Guard: GET /workspace/modules
Guard -> DB: Read tenant module entitlement
DB --> Guard: ATTENDANCE active
Guard --> Web: Entitled module catalog

HR -> Web: Save timezone, weekly offs and working hours
Web -> Guard: PATCH /tenant-settings
Guard -> DB: Validate tenant + settings permission
Guard -> DB: Persist settings
Guard -> Audit: Record configuration change
Guard --> Web: Updated settings

HR -> Web: Create office + geofence
Web -> Config: POST /offices
Config -> Guard: Authorize office management
Config -> DB: Persist coordinates, radius, timezone
Config -> Audit: Record office creation
Config --> Web: Office

HR -> Web: Create shifts / dated rosters
Web -> Config: POST /shifts and /rosters
Config -> Guard: Authorize schedule management
Config -> DB: Persist schedule
Config -> Audit: Record schedule change
Config --> Web: Saved schedule

group Example: office location-only policy
  HR -> Web: Set office geofence, selfie disabled,\nfield tracking disabled
  Web -> Config: POST /attendance-policies
  note right of Web
    locationMode = OFFICE_GEOFENCE
    selfieMode = DISABLED
    fieldTrackingEnabled = false
    requireRegisteredDevice = HR selection
  end note
  Config -> Guard: Authorize policy management
  Config -> Config: Validate entitlement and dependencies
  Config -> DB: Persist versioned policy
  Config -> Audit: Record policy version and actor
  Config --> Web: Policy + warnings/impact
end

HR -> Web: Assign tenant, department or employee policy
Web -> Config: POST /attendance-policy-assignments
Config -> Config: Validate scope and conflicting priority
Config -> DB: Persist assignment
Config -> DB: Increment runtimeConfigVersion
Config -> Audit: Publish tenant.runtime-config.changed.v1
Config --> Web: Assignment saved

HR -> Web: Create/import employee and assign office/shift
Web -> Guard: Employee/import/assignment endpoints
Guard -> DB: Quota, tenant and permission checks
Guard -> DB: Persist employee and assignments
Guard -> Audit: Record lifecycle/assignment changes
Guard --> Web: Employee readiness state

HR -> Web: Invite/link employee account
Web -> Guard: POST /users/invitations
Guard -> DB: Create invitation atomically
Guard -> Audit: Queue invitation event
Guard --> Web: Invitation accepted/queued

== 2. Employee login and dynamic runtime bootstrap ==

Employee -> App: Open DeltCRM and sign in
App -> Guard: POST /auth/login
Guard -> DB: Resolve tenant user + active employee
DB --> Guard: Authenticated employee context
Guard --> App: Access/refresh tokens

App -> Runtime: GET /mobile/runtime-config
Runtime -> Guard: Validate active employee and runtime permission
Runtime -> DB: Read tenant modules/settings/branding
Runtime -> Resolver: Resolve effective Attendance policy
Resolver -> DB: Read employee/department/tenant assignments
Resolver --> Runtime: Winning policy + precedence reason
Runtime -> DB: Read office/device/consent/enrollment readiness
Runtime --> App: Tenant brand + modules + effective capabilities + ETag

note over Runtime,App
  Location-only projection:
  Attendance enabled
  OFFICE_GEOFENCE
  selfie DISABLED
  field tracking disabled
  location permission required
  no biometric onboarding
end note

alt Registered device is required and not approved
  App -> Guard: POST /devices/register
  Guard -> DB: Create PENDING_APPROVAL registration
  Guard -> Audit: Notify HR device queue
  Guard --> App: Pending approval
  HR -> Web: Review employee device
  Web -> Guard: POST /devices/{id}/approve + reason
  Guard -> DB: Activate trusted device
  Guard -> Audit: Record approval
  Guard --> Web: Approved
  App -> Runtime: Refresh runtime configuration
  Runtime --> App: Device readiness complete
else Registered device is optional or already approved
  App -> App: Continue onboarding
end

alt Location required
  App -> GPS: Request foreground precise location
  GPS --> App: Granted / denied
  alt Permission denied
    App --> Employee: Explain requirement; block punch
  end
end

alt Selfie REQUIRED
  App -> Camera: Request consent, enrollment and camera
  Camera --> App: Face readiness
else Selfie DISABLED
  App -> App: Skip camera, consent and face enrollment
end

alt Field tracking enabled and entitled
  App -> GPS: Request background location when field session starts
else Field tracking disabled
  App -> App: Hide field tab; never request background location
end

== 3. Location-only check-in ==

Employee -> App: Tap Check in
App -> GPS: Capture current precise position
GPS --> App: latitude, longitude, accuracy, mock flag
App -> Integrity: Request integrity/attestation evidence
Integrity --> App: Signed integrity token

note right of App
  No selfie is captured or uploaded
  because selfieMode = DISABLED.
end note

App -> Verify: POST /attendance/punches
note right of Verify
  type = CHECKIN
  requestId = idempotency key
  clientTime
  GPS evidence
  device identity + integrity token
  no selfieKey
end note

Verify -> Guard: Validate JWT tenant, employee and entitlement
Guard --> Verify: Authorized employee context
Verify -> DB: Load employee, effective policy, office and device
Verify -> Resolver: Re-resolve effective policy server-side
Resolver --> Verify: OFFICE_GEOFENCE + selfie DISABLED
Verify -> Integrity: Validate integrity token
Integrity --> Verify: Genuine / rooted / mock result

alt Integrity unavailable or invalid
  Verify -> Audit: Record failed verification
  Verify --> App: INTEGRITY_FAILED / PROVIDER_UNAVAILABLE
  App --> Employee: Actionable failure and retry
else Integrity passes
  Verify -> Verify: Validate client clock skew and duplicate requestId
  Verify -> DB: Find assigned active office geofence
  Verify -> Verify: Validate accuracy and calculate distance

  alt No office / poor accuracy / outside geofence
    Verify -> Audit: Record location failure evidence
    Verify --> App: Coded location failure + safe details
    App --> Employee: Enable GPS or move inside approved office
  else Inside assigned office geofence
    Verify -> Verify: Mark face check policy-skipped
    Verify -> Attendance: Apply CHECKIN event
    Attendance -> DB: Lock employee/day and write event + daily record
    Attendance -> Audit: Write verification, audit and outbox atomically
    DB --> Attendance: Committed Attendance state
    Attendance --> Verify: Server-confirmed check-in
    Verify --> App: 201 + verification checks + Attendance state
    App --> Employee: Check-in successful
  end
end

== 4. Check-out, correction and month-end ==

Employee -> App: Tap Check out
App -> GPS: Capture required location again
App -> Integrity: Request fresh integrity evidence
App -> Verify: POST /attendance/punches (CHECKOUT)
Verify -> Attendance: Repeat current effective-policy verification
Attendance -> DB: Write checkout and finalize worked minutes
Attendance -> Audit: Publish finalized Attendance event
Attendance --> App: Completed day
App --> Employee: Show timeline and totals

opt Employee reports missing/incorrect punch
  Employee -> App: Submit correction with reason and requested times
  App -> Attendance: POST /attendance/regularizations
  Attendance -> DB: Create PENDING request
  Attendance -> Audit: Notify authorized HR/manager
  Attendance --> App: Request submitted

  HR -> Web: Review request and evidence
  Web -> Attendance: Approve/reject with comment
  Attendance -> DB: Check manager scope and payroll lock
  alt Period unlocked and request approved
    Attendance -> DB: Apply correction and recalculate daily record
    Attendance -> Audit: Record decision and changed values
    Attendance --> Web: Corrected Attendance state
  else Rejected or period locked
    Attendance --> Web: Coded rejection/locked response
  end
end

HR -> Web: Generate period report
Web -> Reporting: POST /reports
Reporting -> DB: Validate entitlement, permission and period
Reporting -> Audit: Queue report job
Reporting --> Web: QUEUED report
Reporting -> DB: Read finalized tenant-scoped Attendance
Reporting -> Audit: Store completed private report metadata
Reporting --> Web: COMPLETED + expiring download

HR -> Web: Review export and lock payroll period
Web -> Reporting: POST /payroll-locks
Reporting -> DB: Validate completed immutable export
Reporting -> DB: Persist period lock
Reporting -> Audit: Record lock actor, reason and checksum
Reporting --> Web: Locked period

note over Attendance,Reporting
  Mutations affecting a locked payroll period fail closed
  until an authorized, audited reopen operation succeeds.
end note

@enduml
